# =============================================================================
# MASTER ENV TEMPLATE
# Copy this to .env and fill in your values:   cp .env.example .env
# Store actual secrets in Vaultwarden. NEVER commit .env (blocked by .gitignore).
#
# Style: each note sits on its own line ABOVE the variable, and value lines are
# bare KEY=value (no trailing inline comments) — so no parser ever folds a
# comment into a value, and disabling a var is a clean "#KEY=value".
#
# Sections, in order:
#   1. SYSTEM / PATHS / PORTS          — identity, storage, host ports
#   2. GENERATED SECRETS   [SETS]      — bootstrap.sh auto-fills these blanks
#   3. APP KEYS & LOGINS   [LOGIN]     — you set in each app, paste here
#                                        (or run ./scripts/harvest-keys.sh)
#   4. EXTERNAL SERVICES               — VPN + remote-access tokens
#   5. OPTIONAL / NOT YET ENABLED      — commented until you turn them on
#
# [SETS]  = the value here configures the app/DB. For an EXISTING database you
#           MUST reuse its original password or the app won't connect; bootstrap
#           detects existing DBs and leaves them blank.
# [LOGIN] = the app owns the value; wrong value only blanks a Homepage widget,
#           it can never corrupt your data.
#
# Many vars are shared across stacks (globals, ports the dashboard mirrors, a few
# cross-stack keys). For the full model + guidance on splitting stacks onto
# separate hosts, see "How Stacks Connect" in the README.
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
# 1a. SYSTEM
# =============================================================================
# Your server's local IP address
SERVER_IP=192.168.1.100
# Run: id -u
PUID=1000
# Run: id -g
PGID=1000
# TZ database format
TZ=America/Chicago
UMASK=002
# Jellyfin Intel HW transcoding: host render-group GID (getent group render | cut -d: -f3).
# Leave blank to fall back to the container's "render" group.
RENDER_GID=

# Homepage host allow-list. Blank = SERVER_IP:HOMEPAGE_PORT. Add any other names
# you open Homepage by (comma-separated) — Tailscale name, reverse-proxy domain,
# localhost:3000 — or Homepage shows a blank "host validation failed" page.
HOMEPAGE_ALLOWED_HOSTS=

# =============================================================================
# 1b. PATHS
#   Keep CONFIG_PATH on LOCAL disk — databases corrupt on NFS/CIFS.
#   Only MEDIA/PHOTOS/DOCS should ever live on a NAS.
# =============================================================================
# App config + databases (LOCAL disk)
CONFIG_PATH=/opt/docker/data
# Movies, TV, music, anime, books
MEDIA_PATH=/mnt/media
# Immich photo/video library
PHOTOS_PATH=/mnt/photos
# Paperless document storage
DOCS_PATH=/mnt/documents
# Syncthing synced folders
SYNC_PATH=/mnt/sync
# This repo's location — Arcane's projects dir (bootstrap sets it to the real path)
STACKS_PATH=/opt/docker/stacks

# SABnzbd scratch — incomplete downloads + par2 verify/repair + unpack. Keep on a
# FAST LOCAL disk (SSD/NVMe), NOT the NAS: that work is heavy random I/O and stalls
# over a network mount. Only the FINISHED file is moved to the NAS (complete dir),
# so the *arr still hardlink it into the library — they need no access to this path.
INCOMPLETE_PATH=/opt/docker/incomplete

# Tdarr transcode scratch (COMPOSE_PROFILES=tdarr). Needs FREE SPACE — it writes
# the re-encoded file here before swapping it in. Local disk, NOT the NAS.
TDARR_CACHE=/opt/docker/tdarr-cache

# Optional Navidrome music source override (default: ${MEDIA_PATH}/music).
# Most media apps (Jellyfin, *arr, Bazarr, Audiobookshelf) mount the whole media
# root at /data and you pick folders inside the app — so they need no path vars.
# Navidrome is the exception: /data is its own database dir and it has no in-app
# library picker, so its music folder is a dedicated mount you can repoint here.
# MUSIC_PATH=/mnt/media/music

# =============================================================================
# 1c. PORTS — single source of truth for every host port.
# Every port is read by its own stack AND by the dashboard (Homepage), which
# forwards them as HOMEPAGE_VAR_* (see dashboard/docker-compose.yml) — so all
# ports are effectively shared with the dashboard stack; don't duplicate them.
# =============================================================================
# ---- Infrastructure / management ----
NPM_PORT=81
HOMEPAGE_PORT=3000
ARCANE_PORT=3552
# AdGuard admin UI (in infrastructure stack; DNS fixed on :53)
ADGUARD_PORT=3003
# web UI (sync uses 22000, discovery 21027)
SYNCTHING_PORT=8384
# ntfy push hub (in monitoring stack)
NTFY_PORT=9933
# ---- Monitoring ----
UPTIME_KUMA_PORT=3001
DOZZLE_PORT=3002
DIUN_PORT=8085
# ---- Media ----
BITTORRENT_PORT=8080
SABNZBD_PORT=8081
JELLYFIN_PORT=8096
PLEX_PORT=32400
TDARR_PORT=8265
SEERR_PORT=5055
RADARR_PORT=7878
SONARR_PORT=8989
LIDARR_PORT=8686
WHISPARR_PORT=6969
PROWLARR_PORT=9696
BAZARR_PORT=6767
FLARESOLVERR_PORT=8191
AUDIOBOOKSHELF_PORT=13378
NAVIDROME_PORT=4533
# ---- Household ----
MEALIE_PORT=9925
KITCHENOWL_PORT=9926
DONETICK_PORT=9927
ACTUAL_PORT=9928
# ---- Records / knowledge ----
PAPERLESS_PORT=9929
STIRLING_PORT=9931
DOCUSEAL_PORT=9932
MEMOS_PORT=5230
# ---- Vaultwarden ----
VAULTWARDEN_PORT=9930
# Public HTTPS URL when behind a reverse proxy / Cloudflare Tunnel
# (e.g. https://vault.${DOMAIN}). Needed for WebAuthn 2FA, attachments, email
# links and the /admin panel. Leave BLANK for LAN-only http access.
VAULTWARDEN_DOMAIN=
# ---- Cloud ----
IMMICH_PORT=2283
MATRIX_PORT=8008
# ---- Fitness ----
WGER_PORT=9935


# =============================================================================
# 2. GENERATED SECRETS   [SETS]
# bootstrap.sh fills any blank below with a random value. It SKIPS a DB
# password if that database's data dir already exists (so it can't orphan an
# existing DB) — in that case paste the original password yourself.
# Store the final values in Vaultwarden.
# =============================================================================
# Nginx Proxy Manager database  (first init only; existing DB must match)
NPM_DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=
NPM_DB_PASSWORD=

# Vaultwarden  (admin token gates the /admin panel — openssl rand -base64 48)
# First run ONLY: set VAULTWARDEN_SIGNUPS_ALLOWED=true, redeploy, create your
# account in the web UI, then set it back to false and redeploy (signups stay
# off after). gen-secrets fills the admin token automatically.
VAULTWARDEN_SIGNUPS_ALLOWED=false
VAULTWARDEN_ADMIN_TOKEN=

# Paperless  (DB password = first init only; admin user/pass created on first
#             run only — change later in-app, not here)
PAPERLESS_DB_PASSWORD=
# openssl rand -base64 48
PAPERLESS_SECRET_KEY=
PAPERLESS_ADMIN_USER=admin
PAPERLESS_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Immich database  (first init only; existing DB must match)
IMMICH_DB_PASSWORD=

# Donetick  (JWT secret — Donetick refuses to start with a weak/placeholder one)
DONETICK_JWT_SECRET=

# Arcane  (Docker management UI — needs an encryption key + JWT secret)
# bootstrap generates these; or make your own: openssl rand -base64 32
ARCANE_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
ARCANE_JWT_SECRET=

# wger (fitness) — Django keys + DB password
# (DB password = first init only; an existing wger DB must reuse its original)
WGER_DB_PASSWORD=
WGER_SECRET_KEY=
WGER_SIGNING_KEY=


# =============================================================================
# 3. APP KEYS & LOGINS   [LOGIN]
# Create/find each value IN THE APP, then paste it here. Easiest: harvest-keys.sh
# Most of these only feed Homepage widgets (the dashboard stack) — a wrong value
# just blanks a widget, never your data.
# SHARED EXCEPTION — these are ALSO used by the mediastack itself (qBittorrent +
# decluttarr/unpackerr/recyclarr), so a standalone mediastack needs them too:
#   APP_USERNAME, APP_PASSWORD, SABNZBD_API_KEY,
#   SONARR_API_KEY, RADARR_API_KEY, LIDARR_API_KEY
# (The other keys here are dashboard-widget-only.)
# =============================================================================
# Downloads — qBittorrent WebUI login (set in qBit, then match here) + SABnzbd
APP_USERNAME=
APP_PASSWORD=
# SABnzbd → Config → General → Security
SABNZBD_API_KEY=

# *arr — harvest-keys.sh AUTO-DETECTS these from each app's config.xml after
# first boot (or grab manually: app → Settings → General → Security). Bazarr is
# config.yaml-based, so it stays a manual paste.
SONARR_API_KEY=
RADARR_API_KEY=
LIDARR_API_KEY=
WHISPARR_API_KEY=
PROWLARR_API_KEY=
BAZARR_API_KEY=

# Media servers
# Dashboard → API Keys → "+"
JELLYFIN_API_KEY=
# Settings → General → API Key
SEERR_API_KEY=
# your Navidrome username
NAVIDROME_USER=
# md5(password + salt) — harvest-keys.sh can compute this for you
NAVIDROME_TOKEN=
# any random string you choose
NAVIDROME_SALT=
# Settings → Users → your user → API Token
AUDIOBOOKSHELF_TOKEN=

# Household
# profile → API Tokens → Generate
MEALIE_API_KEY=

# Cloud
# Account Settings → API Keys → New
IMMICH_API_KEY=

# Infrastructure — Nginx Proxy Manager login (for the Homepage widget)
NPM_EMAIL=
NPM_PASSWORD=

# Infrastructure — AdGuard Home login (for the Homepage widget)
ADGUARD_USERNAME=
ADGUARD_PASSWORD=


# =============================================================================
# 4. EXTERNAL SERVICES
# =============================================================================
# VPN — WireGuard / ProtonVPN  (REQUIRED for the media downloaders / Gluetun)
VPN_SERVICE_PROVIDER=protonvpn
VPN_TYPE=wireguard
WIREGUARD_PRIVATE_KEY=
WIREGUARD_ADDRESSES=
VPN_SERVER_COUNTRIES=
VPN_PORT_FORWARDING=on
VPN_PORT_FORWARDING_PROVIDER=protonvpn

# Diun — image-update notifier → Home Assistant webhook
# Create in HA: Settings → Automations → New → Webhook trigger
# Format: http://<ha-vm-ip>:8123/api/webhook/<your-webhook-id>
DIUN_NOTIF_WEBHOOK_URL=

# Tailscale — auth key: login.tailscale.com/admin/settings/keys
TS_AUTHKEY=
TAILSCALE_HOSTNAME=homeserver
TAILSCALE_SUBNET=192.168.1.0/24

# Cloudflare Tunnel — token: cloudflare.com → Zero Trust → Networks → Tunnels
CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN=
# Compose profiles — a comma-list that selects which optional/variant services
# run. Read natively by docker compose, so Arcane, hs, AND plain `docker compose`
# all honor it (no script needed). Includes your MEDIA SERVER choice.
# Media server: "jellyfin" (default) or "plex". Optional add-ons (combine freely):
#   tunnel = cloudflared   backup = borgmatic   vpn = tailscale
#   ddns = cloudflare-ddns  matrix = synapse
# e.g. COMPOSE_PROFILES=jellyfin,tunnel,backup   (Plex claim token: PLEX_CLAIM=)
COMPOSE_PROFILES=jellyfin

# Domain / TLS / DDNS  (see docs/network-and-remote-access.md)
#   DOMAIN                  your registered domain; services live at *.${DOMAIN}
#   CLOUDFLARE_DNS_API_TOKEN  scoped token (Zone → DNS → Edit) used by NPM's
#                           wildcard DNS-01 cert AND the ddns-updater container
#   DDNS_DOMAINS            the names whose A record tracks your dynamic WAN IP
#                           (Jellyfin is served direct, NOT via the tunnel)
DOMAIN=example.com
CLOUDFLARE_DNS_API_TOKEN=
DDNS_DOMAINS=jellyfin.example.com


# =============================================================================
# 5. OPTIONAL / NOT YET ENABLED
# Uncomment a block when you turn the matching service on.
# =============================================================================
# Gitea + Actions runner (Phase 3 — devops/)
# GITEA_HTTP_PORT=3030
# GITEA_SSH_PORT=222
# GITEA_DB_PASSWORD=
# GITEA_RUNNER_TOKEN=

# Email / SMTP (Phase 2 — unlocks DocuSeal, Vaultwarden invites, reset emails)
# DOCUSEAL_SECRET_KEY=
# SMTP_ADDRESS=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
# SMTP_FROM=

# Matrix (COMPOSE_PROFILES=matrix) — set to your domain before enabling
MATRIX_SERVER_NAME=

# Borgmatic (COMPOSE_PROFILES=backup) — set your own passphrase before enabling;
# DO NOT lose it (it's required to restore the encrypted backups)
BORG_PASSPHRASE=
